      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Am I inconvenienced by the Transport Workers Union strike? Absolutely. But I am far more disturbed by the double-dealing, switch-and-bait tactics of the M.T.A.</p>
        <p>If a strike, lamentable as it is, is what it will take for that agency and the powers-that-be to acknowledge and fairly address the needs of current and future working New Yorkers, I, for one, am willing to walk.</p>
        <p>Bethany L. Rogers  New York, Dec. 20, 2005</p>
      </block>
